[%- SET title = "Perl on Win32" -%]
[%- PROCESS "blocks.tt2" -%]
[%- WRAPPER wrap_html -%]

[% INCLUDE win32_intro %]

<p>
Perl code can be written to run perfectly on both Windows and UNIXes, out
of the box. Most Perl code written by people who know what they are doing
will be like that, and this is the case for most CPAN Perl modules as well.
</p>

